cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CR

The paper deals with unsupervised learning and topic discovery in large distributed data center networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the use of a non-parametric change-point detection algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with error messages and their separation, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
